The paper deals with the problem of variable selection for sparse linear regression, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper uses complexity theory to prove that finding a sparse vector x that satisfies certain conditions is computationally hard, even under certain assumptions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), or social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories of arXiv CS.
